ce:section.ce:para:
The Co-Pi cocatalyst was further deposited on the BiVO4 and BiVO4-BiOI photoanodes to improve the surface water oxidation kinetic (Fig. 6
                     ). After the modification of Co-Pi, the water oxidation photocurrent density of BiVO4-BiOI simple measured in 0.5 M KH2PO4 is remarkably increased from 0.48 mA cm−2 to 2.59 mA cm−2 (1.23 V
                     RHE), which is also significantly higher than that of the BiVO4/Co-Pi photoanode (1.45 mA cm−2). From above results, one can confirm that the decoration of BiOI and Co-Pi modification on BiVO4 can simultaneously improve the charge separation in the bulk and transfer efficiency on the surface, resulting in the significant improvement in the PEC performance of BiVO4 photoanode. The calculated maximum value of ABPE is 0.79 % at 0.76 VRHE, and there is still much room for improvement if comparing with the theoretical value.
